  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at combating money laundering:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- Sets global standards for anti-money laundering policies\n- Develops recommendations for preventing financial crimes\n- 39 member jurisdictions collaborate to implement guidelines\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention Against Corruption\n- Provide frameworks for international cooperation\n\n3. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Establishes global banking regulations\n- Provides guidance on preventing money laundering\n\n4. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Guidelines\n- Assists countries in developing anti-money laundering frameworks\n- Provides technical assistance and policy recommendations\n\n5. Individual Country Legislation\n- Many nations have implemented domestic laws like:\n- U.S. Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Financial intelligence units track suspicious transactions\n\nThese international efforts aim to create consistent global standards for detecting, preventing, and prosecuting money laundering activities.",
